  "prompt": "How widely accepted are credit cards at small businesses and restaurants in Malta?",
  "response": "Credit card acceptance at small businesses and restaurants in Malta has been increasing over the years, but it can vary significantly from place to place. In urban areas and popular tourist regions, most small businesses and restaurants are likely to accept credit cards. However, in more remote or less tourist-heavy areas, some establishments may prefer cash or have a minimum spend requirement for card payments.\n\nIt's always a good idea to carry some cash, especially when visiting smaller shops or local eateries, as they may not always have the capability to process card transactions. Additionally, the types of credit cards accepted can vary, with Visa and MasterCard being the most commonly accepted brands, while American Express and others might not be as widely supported.\n\nAs of the latest trends, mobile payment options and digital wallets are also gaining traction, which may provide additional payment alternatives even in smaller businesses. Always check in advance or ask when you enter a shop or restaurant to confirm their payment methods.",
